{
  "stem": "5356.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Their stomachs couldn't cope with all that fat food and all the things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they died of dysentery.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And you looked at the people, I mean, it was mussulmens.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I mean, you can only hold on for so long.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then you just give up, your hope.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Doesn't work like a machine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You can only go so far.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And that's-- that's what it is.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Americans came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, it was euphoria that you survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You looked around you, and you saw what happened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because while you're there, you're not thinking of anything else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But you're thinking of food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Here, you ready-- the food question wasn't the problem.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because right away, you know, there was food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So you looked-- you realized what's happening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because your mind, your eyes, saw something else.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you saw before you were just worried about yourself to survive, not get beaten up, not go someplace where you'll be taken away or have something done to you.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But afterwards, you realized what had happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember, the two days later when they brought in the Germans from Weimar, because Weimar was only 8 kilometers away, to show them what happened and they say-- them saying, you know, we didn't know nothing.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, Buchenwald had a crematorium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it was only for dead people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It wasn't like live people to be burned, like Auschwitz or Birkenau or some place else.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So the only time where the-- they kept us busy was they took us a couple of times to Weimar before the liberation to clean the city, you know, after bombardments.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were there in the city while bombs were falling in Weimar.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And twice, they did that-- I was there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You know, and you approach the Buchenwald gate, you see [SPEAKING GERMAN]",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
